docs.name: Zillow Metrics (Cities): Sold for Loss (%) - Vineland, NJ
docs.description: The percentage of homes that sold for less than the previous purchase price (e.g. a home purchased for $250k and then sold for $225k). This excludes foreclosure transactions. This data is calculated by Zillow Real Estate Research (www.zillow.com/research) using their database of 110 million homes.

sources.description: Zillow is an online real estate database that was founded in 2005 and created by Rich Barton and Lloyd Frink, former Microsoft executives and founders of Microsoft spin-off Expedia. Spencer Rascoff is the current CEO of Zillow, Inc.
